Name: signal
Description: tunneled content to be processed silently

Name: alert
Description:
the body is a custom ring tone to alert the    
user

Name: icon
Description: the body is displayed as an icon to the user

Name: render
Description: the body should be displayed to the user

Name: recipient-list-history
Description:
the body contains a list of URIs that          
indicates the recipients of the request

Name: session
Description:
the body describes a communications session,   
for example, an RFC2327 SDP body

Name: early-session
Description:
the body describes an early communications     
session, for example, and [RFC2327] SDP body

Name: recipient-list
Description:
The body includes a list of URIs to which      
URI-list services are to be applied.

Name: notification
Description:
the payload of the message carrying this       
Content-Disposition header field value is
an Instant Message Disposition Notification
as requested in the corresponding Instant
Message.

Name: by-reference
Description:
The body needs to be handled according to a    
reference to the body that is located in
the same SIP message as the body.

Name: info-package
Description:
The body contains information associated with an 
Info Package

Name: recording-session
Description:
The body describes either metadata about the RS or the reason
        for the metadata snapshot request as determined by the MIME
        value indicated in the Content-Type.
